The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Bhopal, April 6 (PTI): A trainee aircraft today sank in the Bargi reservoir in Seoni district. The fate of its pilot is not known, police said.          
	The aircraft belonged to the Chimes Aviation Academy in Sagar. It took off around 2.30pm for a training sortie. The academys chief operating officer, Y.N. Sharma, identified the pilot as Rituraj from Jharkhand.                   
	 Mumbai: The Mumbai terror attack case will begin on April 15 in the high-security court at Arthur Road jail. Sessions court judge M.L. Tahilyani has extended the custody of Ajmal Kasab and two other accused and told special public prosecutor Ujjwal Nikam to deliver his opening address in the court on April 15.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): An army jawan committed suicide using his service rifle in Anantnag district on Monday, a police spokesman said. Sepoy Mohammad Kartik was posted with 36 Rashtriya Rifles. The suicide would be investigated, the spokesman said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Activist Medha Patkar, who is facing a bailable warrant issued by a Gujarat court in connection with a defamation case, has approached the Supreme Court seeking its transfer to a Delhi court. The case had been filed against Patkar for her alleged defamatory remarks during a TV debate on the Sardar Sarovar dam.                   
	 Mysore (PTI): Ram Sena leader Pramod Muthalik was taken into preventive custody on Monday, police said. He was visiting the Kyatharamanhalli suburb, where clashes had taken place after prohibitory orders were issued.                  
	 Thane (PTI): At least three persons died when a building being demolished by municipal authorities collapsed on Monday, police said. Civic authorities had begun the demolition of the three-storeyed structure when a portion collapsed around 11am.                                                                                                                           
